## Interview Definition

### Client–Server Model
A client–server model is a computing architecture in which a client (device or application) sends requests to a server, and the server processes those requests and returns the appropriate response.

### Pay-as-You-Go
AWS follows a pay-as-you-go pricing model, where customers pay only for the cloud resources they consume and stop paying when those resources are no longer in use.

